Morning Pages
What is this?
Morning Pages is a daily writing practice rooted in Julia Cameron's The Artist's Way. The idea: write three pages of unfiltered, stream-of-consciousness words every morning. No editing. No judgment. Just words.

This app gives that practice a gentle home — tracking your progress, honoring your consistency, and celebrating every milestone.

Writing
Three pages = 750 words. Write freely in the lined area.
Your word count never decreases — deletions don't cost you progress.
Pages auto-save every 3 seconds. Use save ✦ to save manually.
Each completed day is sealed at midnight (or your custom time) and becomes read-only.
Calendar dots
🤍 — day completed
🦉 — completed after 9 PM
💔 — day missed
🩹 — missed day repaired
Click any dot with writing in it to read that day's entry.
Streaks & repair
Your streak builds day by day. Milestones unlock at 3, 7, 14, 30, 90, 150, 180, 365, 500, 730, and 1095 days.
Miss some days? If you return within a window equal to your old streak length, you'll be offered streak repair.
Repair works by writing double days (6 pages / 1500 words) — one per missed day. Each earns a 🩹.
Once all days are mended, your streak reflects the full unbroken count.
Night owl mode 🦉
Click the owl to set a custom "new day begins at" time — helpful if you write late at night.
Writing completed after 9 PM earns an owl emoji on your calendar instead of a heart.
Bottom bar
⏳ — tap the hourglass to show or hide the session timer.
The ⛵ sails as you write; it becomes a 🏝️ when you reach your goal.
Page sheets stack up as you write — one sheet per 250 words.
Word milestones
Lifetime milestones unlock at 1k, 2k, 5k, 7.5k, 10k, 20k, 50k, 75k, 100k, 250k, 500k, 750k, and 1 million words — each with a celebration and a fun fact.
